{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idaa7f0e25-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4508"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4508"},"text":"§ 4508.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Contractor performance of acquisition functions closely associated with inherently governmental functions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idaa7f0e26-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4508/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Limitation","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The head of an agency may enter into a contract for the performance of acquisition functions closely associated with inherently governmental functions only if the contracting officer for the contract ensures that—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa7f0e27-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4508/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" appropriate military or civilian personnel of the Department of Defense cannot reasonably be made available to perform the functions;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa7f0e28-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4508/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" appropriate military or civilian personnel of the Department of Defense are—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa7f0e29-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4508/a/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to supervise contractor performance of the contract; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa7f0e2a-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4508/a/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to perform all inherently governmental functions associated with the functions to be performed under the contract; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa7f0e2b-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4508/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the agency addresses any potential organizational conflict of interest of the contractor in the performance of the functions under the contract, consistent with subpart 9.5 of part 9 of the Federal Acquisition Regulation and the best interests of the Department of Defense.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idaa7f0e2c-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4508/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Definitions","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In this section:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa7f0e2d-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4508/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “head of an agency” does not include the Secretary of Homeland Security or the Administrator of the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa7f0e2e-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4508/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “inherently governmental functions” has the meaning given such term in subpart 7.5 of part 7 of the Federal Acquisition Regulation.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa7f0e2f-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4508/b/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “functions closely associated with inherently governmental functions” means the functions described in section 7.503(d) of the Federal Acquisition Regulation.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa7f0e30-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4508/b/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “organizational conflict of interest” has the meaning given such term in subpart 9.5 of part 9 of the Federal Acquisition Regulation.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idaa7f0e31-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/375/dA/tVIII/s804/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–375, div. A, title VIII, § 804(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-10-28"},"text":"Oct. 28, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/2007"},"text":"118 Stat. 2007","children":[],"tail":", § 2383; renumbered § 4508 and amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/dA/tXVIII/s1856/g"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, div. A, title XVIII, § 1856(g)","children":[],"tail":", (i), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/4275"},"text":"134 Stat. 4275","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idaa7f0e32-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idaa7f0e33-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"idaa7f0e34-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 4508, acts ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041"},"text":"Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/253"},"text":"70A Stat. 253","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1966-11-02"},"text":"Nov. 2, 1966","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/718/s27"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–718, § 27","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/80/1119"},"text":"80 Stat. 1119","children":[],"tail":", which related tests of iron, steel, and other materials, was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/160/dA/tVIII/s822/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–160, div. A, title VIII, § 822(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1993-11-30"},"text":"Nov. 30, 1993","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/107/1706"},"text":"107 Stat. 1706","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idaa7f0e35-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14